{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866166232,"sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","part":{"id":"prt_d79df2c5d001fVA3Iav40dgWza","messageID":"msg_d79df1d13001aFIJTQnx7NkUmq","sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c055f9be1d0546ce81d38def","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型增强\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: 增强 MetadataService 和数据模型，实现完整的元数据生命周期管理和验证功能。\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: `AgentMetadata` 和 `MetadataService` 是 CLI 核心的元数据管理组件。当前实现存在以下问题:\n12: 1. `AgentMetadata` 位于 `services` 包，而非 `models` 包\n13: 2. 缺少 `update_metadata` 方法\n14: 3. 缺少语言特定的工作区验证\n15: 4. `MetadataOptions` 缺少 `from_options` 类方法\n16: \n17: ### Goal\n18: \n19: 1. 迁移 AgentMetadata 到 models 包统一管理\n20: 2. 实现完整的 MetadataService CRUD 操作\n21: 3. 添加语言特定验证逻辑\n22: 4. 增强 MetadataOptions\n23: \n24: ### Value\n25: \n26: - **模块化**: 数据模型与业务逻辑分离\n27: - **可维护性**: 统一的模型定义位置\n28: - **完整性**: 完整的元数据生命周期支持\n29: - **可验证性**: 语言特定工作区验证\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## Scope\n34: \n35: ### In-Scope\n36: \n37: | Component | Path | Description |\n38: |-----------|------|-------------|\n39: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/models/agent_models.py` | 新的独立模型文件 |\n40: | MetadataOptions | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | 增强的方法 |\n41: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | 新增方法 |\n42: | Unit tests | `tests/test_metadata_service.py` | 测试覆盖 |\n43: \n44: ### Out-of-Scope\n45: \n46: - CLI 命令参数变更\n47: - Runtime 类修改\n48: - 数据库持久化\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## Impact Analysis\n53: \n54: ### Dependencies\n55: \n56: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n57: |------------|---------|--------|\n58: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | 数据模型验证 | Existing |\n59: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML 序列化 | Existing |\n60: \n61: ### Upstream\n62: \n63: - `cli-toolkit/design.md` — MetadataService 设计\n64: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — 元数据需求\n65: \n66: ### Downstream Consumers\n67: \n68: 1. **PackRuntime** — 元数据加载和验证\n69: 2. **BuildRuntime** — 版本管理\n70: 3. **PublishRuntime** — 部署信息\n71: 4. **InvokeRuntime** — 端点信息\n72: \n73: ### Risks\n74: \n75: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n76: |------|----------|------------|\n77: | Import 变更 | Medium | 保持向后兼容导出 |\n78: | 破坏性变更 | High | 添加兼容层 |\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Alternatives Considered\n83: \n84: ### Option 1: 保持现状 (Not Selected)\n85: \n86: 仅添加缺失方法，不移动模型位置。\n87: \n88: **Cons**:\n89: - 模型定义位置不合理\n90: - 不符合设计 spec\n91: \n92: ### Option 2: 完全重构 (Selected)\n93: \n94: 迁移 AgentMetadata 到 models 包，增强 MetadataService。\n95: \n96: **Pros**:\n97: - 符合设计规范\n98: - 模块化更好\n99: - 便于维护\n100: \n101: **Cons**:\n102: - 需要更新多个 import\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Implementation Plan\n107: \n108: ### Phase 1: 模型迁移\n109: - [ ] 创建 `agentcube/models/agent_models.py`\n110: - [ ] 移动 AgentMetadata 到新文件\n111: - [ ] 更新 models/__init__.py 导出\n112: - [ ] 更新 services/metadata_service.py import\n113: \n114: ### Phase 2: MetadataService 增强\n115: - [ ] 实现 `update_metadata` 方法\n116: - [ ] 实现 `_validate_python_workspace` 方法\n117: - [ ] 实现 `_validate_java_workspace` 方法\n118: - [ ] 更新 save_metadata 使用 exclude_none\n119: \n120: ### Phase 3: MetadataOptions 增强\n121: - [ ] 添加 `from_options` 类方法\n122: - [ ] 确保字段默认值一致\n123: \n124: ### Phase 4: 测试\n125: - [ ] 更新现有测试 import\n126: - [ ] 添加新方法测试\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## Acceptance Criteria\n131: \n132: ### AgentMetadata 模型\n133: \n134: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n135: |----|----------|-----------------|\n136: | AM-001 | 导出路径 | `from agentcube.models import AgentMetadata` 可用 |\n137: | AM-002 | 字段验证 | language 只能是 python/java |\n138: | AM-003 | 字段验证 | port 范围 1-65535 |\n139: | AM-004 | 默认值 | language 默认为 python |\n140: \n141: ### MetadataService\n142: \n143: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n144: |----|----------|-----------------|\n145: | MS-001 | load_metadata | 正确加载 agent_metadata.yaml |\n146: | MS-002 | save_metadata | 使用 exclude_none=True |\n147: | MS-003 | update_metadata | 正确合并更新并保存 |\n148: | MS-004 | validate_python | 无 .py 文件时抛出 ValueError |\n149: | MS-005 | validate_java | 无 pom.xml 时抛出 ValueError |\n150: \n151: ### MetadataOptions\n152: \n153: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n154: |----|----------|-----------------|\n155: | MO-001 | from_options | 正确从 dict 创建实例 |\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## Technical Design\n160: \n161: ### AgentMetadata 模型\n162: \n163: ```python\n164: # agentcube/models/agent_models.py\n165: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n166: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n167: \n168: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n169:     model_config = {\"extra\": \"forbid\"}\n170:     \n171:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n172:     description: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n173:     language: str = Field(default=\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n174:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n175:     port: int = Field(default=8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n176:     build_mode: str = Field(default=\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n177:     region: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n178:     version: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Semantic version string\")\n179:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(default=None)\n180:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(default=None)\n181:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"requirements.txt\")\n182:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\")\n183:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\")\n184:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\")\n185:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(default=None)\n186:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=None)\n187:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=None)\n188:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(default=None)\n189:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(default=None)\n190:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(default=None)\n191:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(default=None)\n192:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(default=None)\n193: \n194:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n195:     @classmethod\n196:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n197:         v_lower = v.lower()\n198:         if v_lower not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n199:             raise ValueError(\"Language must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n200:         return v_lower\n201: \n202:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n203:     @classmethod\n204:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n205:         v_lower = v.lower()\n206:         if v_lower not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n207:             raise ValueError(\"Build mode must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n208:         return v_lower\n209: \n210:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n211:     @classmethod\n212:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n213:         if not isinstance(v, int):\n214:             raise ValueError(\"Port must be an integer\")\n215:         if v < 1 or v > 65535:\n216:             raise ValueError(\"Port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n217:         return v\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### MetadataService 更新\n221: \n222: ```python\n223: # agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n224: from agentcube.models.agent_models import AgentMetadata\n225: \n226: class MetadataService:\n227:     METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n228: \n229:     @staticmethod\n230:     def load_metadata(workspace_path: str | Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n231:     \n232:     @staticmethod\n233:     def save_metadata(workspace_path: str | Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Path:\n234:         workspace = Path(workspace_path)\n235:         metadata_file = workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n236:         \n237:         with open(metadata_file, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n238:             yaml.safe_dump(\n239:                 metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True), \n240:                 f, \n241:                 default_flow_style=False, \n242:                 sort_keys=False\n243:             )\n244:         return metadata_file\n245: \n246:     @staticmethod\n247:     def update_metadata(workspace_path: str | Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n248:         \"\"\"Load, merge updates, save pattern.\"\"\"\n249:         metadata = MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n250:         updated = metadata.model_copy(update=updates)\n251:         MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated)\n252:         return updated\n253: \n254:     @staticmethod\n255:     def validate_workspace(workspace_path: str | Path) -> bool: ...\n256: \n257:     @staticmethod\n258:     def _validate_python_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n259:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n260:         if not py_files:\n261:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n262: \n263:     @staticmethod\n264:     def _validate_java_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n265:         pom_file = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n266:         if not pom_file.exists():\n267:             raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ### MetadataOptions 增强\n271: \n272: ```python\n273: # agentcube/models/pack_models.py\n274: from dataclasses import dataclass\n275: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n276: \n277: @dataclass\n278: class MetadataOptions:\n279:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n280:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n281:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n282:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n283:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n284:     description: Optional[str] = None\n285:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n286:     output: Optional[str] = None\n287:     verbose: bool = False\n288:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n289:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n290:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n291:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n292:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n293:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n294:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n295:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n296: \n297:     @classmethod\n298:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n299:         \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from CLI options dictionary.\"\"\"\n300:         valid_fields = {f.name for f in cls.__dataclass_fields__.values()}\n301:         filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in valid_fields}\n302:         return cls(**filtered)\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Timeline Estimate\n308: \n309: | Phase | Effort |\n310: |-------|--------|\n311: | 模型迁移 | 1-2 hours |\n312: | MetadataService 增强 | 2 hours |\n313: | MetadataOptions 增强 | 1 hour |\n314: | 测试 | 2 hours |\n315: | **Total** | **6-7 hours** |\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ## Existing Implementation Status\n320: \n321: 当前实现位于:\n322: - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` (139 lines) — AgentMetadata + MetadataService\n323: - `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` (27 lines) — MetadataOptions\n324: \n325: ### Current Gaps\n326: \n327: 1. **模型位置**: AgentMetadata 在 services 包而非 models 包\n328: 2. **缺少 update_metadata**: 设计中要求但未实现\n329: 3. **缺少验证方法**: _validate_python_workspace, _validate_java_workspace 未实现\n330: 4. **MetadataOptions**: 缺少 from_options 类方法\n331: 5. **save_metadata**: 未使用 exclude_none=True\n\n(End of file - total 331 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型增强\n\n## Summary\n\n增强 MetadataService 和数据模型，实现完整的元数据生命周期管理和验证功能。\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\n`AgentMetadata` 和 `MetadataService` 是 CLI 核心的元数据管理组件。当前实现存在以下问题:\n1. `AgentMetadata` 位于 `services` 包，而非 `models` 包\n2. 缺少 `update_metadata` 方法\n3. 缺少语言特定的工作区验证\n4. `MetadataOptions` 缺少 `from_options` 类方法\n\n### Goal\n\n1. 迁移 AgentMetadata 到 models 包统一管理\n2. 实现完整的 MetadataService CRUD 操作","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775866166202,"end":1775866166230}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866166234,"sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","part":{"id":"prt_d79df2ff200182iwhEsV3XHYuI","messageID":"msg_d79df1d13001aFIJTQnx7NkUmq","sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_343a0b67ef06441d8103f2b8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-020\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-020-001: Workspace validation\n25: \n26: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-A — Valid Python workspace\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n31: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n32: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n33: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-B — Valid Java workspace\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n38: - **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n39: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n40: - **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-C — Missing workspace directory\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n45: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n46: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-D — Python workspace without Python files\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n51: - **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-020-001-E — Java workspace without pom.xml\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n57: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### AR-020-002: Metadata loading and merging\n63: \n64: The system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-A — Load existing metadata\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n69: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n71: - **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-B — Fallback metadata file loading\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n76: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n78: - **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-C — Create new metadata with defaults\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n83: - **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n85:   - `language`: `\"python\"`\n86:   - `port`: `8080`\n87:   - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n88:   - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: AR-020-002-D — CLI option overrides\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n93: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n95:   - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n96:   - `--language` overrides `language`\n97:   - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n98:   - `--port` overrides `port`\n99:   - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n100:   - `--description` overrides `description`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### AR-020-003: Dockerfile generation\n105: \n106: The system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-A — Generate Python Dockerfile\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n111: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n113: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Python base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-B — Generate Java Dockerfile\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n118: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n119: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n120: - **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include Maven/Java base image, dependency installation, entrypoint, and port exposure\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AR-020-003-C — Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n125: - **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n127: - **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-020-004: Dependency processing\n132: \n133: The system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-A — Process Python dependencies\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n138: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n139: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-B — Process Java dependencies\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n144: - **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n145: - **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-020-004-C — Missing Python requirements file\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n150: - **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### AR-020-005: Output preparation\n156: \n157: The system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-A — Default output path\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n162: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n163: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-B — Custom output path\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n168: - **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: AR-020-005-C — Update metadata after packaging\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n174: - **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### AR-020-006: CLI interface\n180: \n181: The system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-A — Pack command options\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n186: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n187:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n188:   - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n189:   - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n190:   - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n191:   - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n192:   - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n193:   - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n194:   - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n195:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-B — Successful pack output\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n200: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n201: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n202: - **AND** display agent name, resolved workspace path, and metadata file path\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-C — Pack failure with verbose logging\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n207: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n208: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n209: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: AR-020-006-D — Pack failure without verbose\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n214: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n215: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n216: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### AR-020-007: Language compatibility validation\n221: \n222: The system SHALL validate that the specified language and port are valid.\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-A — Valid language specification\n225: \n226: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n227: - **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n228: - **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-B — Invalid language specification\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n233: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n234: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: AR-020-007-C — Port range validation\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n239: - **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n240: - **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### AR-020-008: Entrypoint inference\n245: \n246: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-A — Infer Python entrypoint\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n251: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n252: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n253: - **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: AR-020-008-B — Infer Java entrypoint\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n258: - **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n259: - **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n260: - **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Acceptance Criteria\n265: \n266: - [ ] AC001: Pack validates workspace structure before processing\n267: - [ ] AC002: Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults\n268: - [ ] AC003: Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata\n269: - [ ] AC004: Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java)\n270: - [ ] AC005: Pack processes dependencies for the target language\n271: - [ ] AC006: Pack prepares output path and saves metadata\n272: - [ ] AC007: Pack displays success output with Rich formatting\n273: - [ ] AC008: Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging\n274: - [ ] AC009: Pack validates language and port values\n275: - [ ] AC010: Pack infers entrypoint when not provided\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Architecture Notes\n280: \n281: ### Key Components\n282: \n283: | Component | Path | Description |\n284: |-----------|------|-------------|\n285: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `pack` command |\n286: | PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core packaging logic |\n287: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n288: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n289: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Dockerfile generation and Docker operations |\n290: \n291: ### Metadata Fields (AgentMetadata)\n292: \n293: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n294: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n295: | agent_name | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n296: | language | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n297: | entrypoint | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n298: | port | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n299: | build_mode | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n300: | description | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n301: | requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n302: \n303: ### CLI Options Mapping\n304: \n305: | CLI Option | Metadata Field | Type |\n306: |------------|----------------|------|\n307: | `--agent-name` | agent_name | Optional[str] |\n308: | `--language` | language | Optional[str] |\n309: | `--entrypoint` | entrypoint | Optional[str] |\n310: | `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n311: | `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n312: | `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n313: | `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## References\n318: \n319: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n320: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n321: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n322: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n323: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n324: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI pack command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-020\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866166206,"end":1775866166233}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866166238,"sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","part":{"id":"prt_d79df37d6001iwnHxbZQT7jF7E","messageID":"msg_d79df1d13001aFIJTQnx7NkUmq","sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6e60a3df68ce404a89419810","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/models/pack_models.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/models/pack_models.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Data models for AgentCube pack command.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from dataclasses import dataclass\n4: from typing import Optional\n5: \n6: \n7: @dataclass\n8: class MetadataOptions:\n9:     \"\"\"CLI options for metadata override.\"\"\"\n10: \n11:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n12:     language: Optional[str] = None\n13:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n14:     port: Optional[int] = None\n15:     build_mode: Optional[str] = None\n16:     description: Optional[str] = None\n17:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n18:     output: Optional[str] = None\n19:     verbose: bool = False\n20:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n21:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n22:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n23:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n24:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n25:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n26:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n27:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Data models for AgentCube pack command.\"\"\"\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"CLI options for metadata override.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = None\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = None\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    output: Optional[str] = None\n    verbose: bool = False\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/models/pack_models.py","time":{"start":1775866166211,"end":1775866166236}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866166240,"sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","part":{"id":"prt_d79df3392001LjI8I6OSaJ0q5D","messageID":"msg_d79df1d13001aFIJTQnx7NkUmq","sessionID":"ses_28620f443ffeOwB10PccdNhCR2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8f7fa8bee82e4bd1b150c1ad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Metadata service for AgentCube - handles agent metadata loading, saving, and validation.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: import os\n6: from pathlib import Path\n7: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n8: \n9: import yaml\n10: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n11: \n12: \n13: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n14:     \"\"\"Pydantic model for agent metadata configuration.\"\"\"\n15: \n16:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n17:     description: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n18:     language: str = Field(default=\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n19:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n20:     port: int = Field(default=8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n21:     build_mode: str = Field(default=\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n22:     region: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n23:     version: Optional[str] = Field(\n24:         default=None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\"\n25:     )\n26:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(default=None, description=\"Container image information\")\n27:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(default=None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n28:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\n29:         default=\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\"\n30:     )\n31:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n32:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n33:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n34:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n35:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(\n36:         default=None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\"\n37:     )\n38:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n39:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(\n40:         default=None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\"\n41:     )\n42:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(\n43:         default=None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\"\n44:     )\n45:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n46:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n47:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(\n48:         default=None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\"\n49:     )\n50: \n51:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n52:     @classmethod\n53:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n54:         \"\"\"Validate that language is either python or java.\"\"\"\n55:         v_lower = v.lower()\n56:         if v_lower not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n57:             raise ValueError(\"Language must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n58:         return v_lower\n59: \n60:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n61:     @classmethod\n62:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n63:         \"\"\"Validate that build_mode is either local or cloud.\"\"\"\n64:         v_lower = v.lower()\n65:         if v_lower not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n66:             raise ValueError(\"Build mode must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n67:         return v_lower\n68: \n69:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n70:     @classmethod\n71:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n72:         \"\"\"Validate that port is in valid range (1-65535).\"\"\"\n73:         if not isinstance(v, int):\n74:             raise ValueError(\"Port must be an integer\")\n75:         if v < 1 or v > 65535:\n76:             raise ValueError(\"Port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n77:         return v\n78: \n79: \n80: class MetadataService:\n81:     \"\"\"Service for managing agent metadata in workspace.\"\"\"\n82: \n83:     METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n84: \n85:     @staticmethod\n86:     def load_metadata(workspace_path: str | Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n87:         \"\"\"\n88:         Load metadata from workspace with fallback chain.\n89: \n90:         Searches for metadata files in order: agent_metadata.yaml -> agent.yaml -> metadata.yaml\n91:         Raises FileNotFoundError if none found.\n92:         \"\"\"\n93:         workspace = Path(workspace_path)\n94: \n95:         for filename in MetadataService.METADATA_FILES:\n96:             metadata_file = workspace / filename\n97:             if metadata_file.exists():\n98:                 with open(metadata_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n99:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n100:                     if data:\n101:                         return AgentMetadata(**data)\n102: \n103:         raise FileNotFoundError(\n104:             f\"No metadata file found in {workspace}. \"\n105:             f\"Expected one of: {', '.join(MetadataService.METADATA_FILES)}\"\n106:         )\n107: \n108:     @staticmethod\n109:     def save_metadata(workspace_path: str | Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Path:\n110:         \"\"\"\n111:         Save metadata to workspace as agent_metadata.yaml.\n112: \n113:         Returns the path to the saved file.\n114:         \"\"\"\n115:         workspace = Path(workspace_path)\n116:         metadata_file = workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n117: \n118:         with open(metadata_file, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n119:             yaml.safe_dump(metadata.model_dump(), f, default_flow_style=False, sort_keys=False)\n120: \n121:         return metadata_file\n122: \n123:     @staticmethod\n124:     def validate_workspace(workspace_path: str | Path) -> bool:\n125:         \"\"\"\n126:         Basic validation that workspace path exists and is a directory.\n127: \n128:         Returns True if valid.\n129:         Raises ValueError if not valid.\n130:         \"\"\"\n131:         workspace = Path(workspace_path)\n132: \n133:         if not workspace.exists():\n134:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path does not exist: {workspace}\")\n135: \n136:         if not workspace.is_dir():\n137:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace}\")\n138: \n139:         return True\n\n(End of file - total 139 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Metadata service for AgentCube - handles agent metadata loading, saving, and validation.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nimport yaml\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Pydantic model for agent metadata configuration.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(default=None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(default=\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(default=8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py","time":{"start":1775866166209,"end":1775866166238}}}}
